dashboard.definition:
{
	"visualizations": {
		"viz_markdown": {
			"type": "splunk.markdown",
			"options": {
				"markdown": "# Problem description\n\nSplunk has reserved keywords which have specific meaning and treatment. These are `index`, `host`, `source` and `sourcetype` should these keywords appear in search results we rename them to prevent a name space clash. However should these values be added explicity as user defined indexed fields in `_meta` we find multi value fields occuring when we have namespace clash. \n\nextracted_host\n\n###  Example namespace clash\n\nThis data structure is generated by the zoom API for a meeting. Inside the data structure we can see a attribute name `host` which is a one of our reserved keywords. Unfortunately the JSON parser does not understand this and generates `host::\"director@cia.us.gov\"` and inserts that into `_meta` causing us headaches at search time. \n\n    {\n        \"host\": \"director@cia.us.gov\",\n        \"uuid\": \"Y=l=SACZfon=MVfUMx/hU/==\",\n        \"id\": 57900665151,\n        \"topic\": \"Splunk> All batbelt. No tights. \",\n        \"email\": \"putin@gru.ru\",\n        \"user_type\": \"Licensed|Large500\",\n        \"start_time\": \"2020-10-26T03:17:31\",\n        \"end_time\": \"2020-10-26T05:35:31\",\n        \"duration\": \"2:18:00\",\n        \"participants\": 12,\n        \"has_pstn\": true,\n        \"has_voip\": true,\n        \"has_3rd_party_audio\": true,\n        \"has_video\": true,\n        \"has_screen_share\": false,\n        \"has_recording\": false,\n        \"has_sip\": false\n    }\n\n## Proposed solution\n\nWe use the alterate syntax for indexed fields in INGEST_EVAL to target the value for host in the pipeline data like so `$pd:host$`, and we use the `$field:host$` syntax to target the user defined one in the `_meta` string.\n\n#### props.conf\n\n    # This demonstrates how to fix clashing names found when using INDEXED_EXTRACTIONS\n    [name_clash]\n    INDEXED_EXTRACTIONS = JSON\n    TIMESTAMP_FIELDS = start_time\n    TIME_FORMAT = %Y-%m-%dT%T\n    TRANSFORMS-rename_host = name_clash_rename_host\n\n#### transforms.conf\n\n    # rename the user defined host into a meeting_host\n    [name_clash_rename_host]\n    INGEST_EVAL = meeting_host:=$field:host$, $field:host$:=null()"
			}
		}
	},
	"dataSources": {},
	"defaults": {
		"dataSources": {
			"ds.search": {
				"options": {
					"queryParameters": {
						"latest": "$global_time.latest$",
						"earliest": "$global_time.earliest$"
					}
				}
			},
			"ds.spl2": {
				"options": {
					"queryParameters": {
						"latest": "$global_time.latest$",
						"earliest": "$global_time.earliest$"
					}
				}
			}
		},
		"visualizations": {
			"global": {
				"showProgressBar": true
			}
		}
	},
	"inputs": {},
	"layout": {
		"options": {},
		"globalInputs": [],
		"tabs": {
			"items": [
				{
					"layoutId": "layout_1",
					"label": "New tab"
				}
			]
		},
		"layoutDefinitions": {
			"layout_1": {
				"type": "grid",
				"structure": [
					{
						"item": "viz_markdown",
						"type": "block",
						"position": {
							"x": 0,
							"y": 0,
							"w": 1440,
							"h": 703
						}
					}
				],
				"options": {
					"width": 1440,
					"height": 960
				}
			}
		}
	},
	"description": "",
	"title": "Name clash"
}
